Phrase: The Senbon Torii appeared in M Nishiki. Vermilion coloured torii lined up in a row from the foot of the small mountain up to the peak, like an approach leading to a temple.

The path created by countless torii branched off in the middle. Paddington's rote memorization ability isn't able to help here, as the path dead-ends at invisible walls, returns to the same place, and other unexplainable bizarre phenomena occured.
--Within this darkness, we continued to wander through the torii labyrinth.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: We've been walking back to where we started for ages now.

Name: Putra
Phrase: It's strange how we keep going up the mountain only to end up in the same place. Is Nishiki's mysterious powers alive and well in the Metro universe too?

Name: Putra
Phrase: Yoshino, how are you feeling? You haven't spoken at all since a while ago, are you over-strained?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Worse than normal. But at a level where it's still OK.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Felt accustomed to it, so the queasiness is subsiding. But head and ears are still going round and round.

Name: Putra
Phrase: It seems like the magic here is affecting you after all. If you think it's impossible, tell us right away, okay?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Un. Keeping physical strength in case of emergency.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Even so, we can't just retreat at a moment's notice in a maze like this...

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Conductor, if we don't know how to proceed after a bit more investigation, shouldn't we turn back?

Name: Putra
Phrase: I think so too. Not just Yoshino, but even Vivienne seems to be somewhat in a bad shape too.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Oh non, did you found out?

Name: Putra
Phrase: I know you well. You can't fool my eyes, okay?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: I was trying to look casual and normal too.

Unfortunately, I am also aware that Vivienne's not feeling well. It seems that those who are more sensitive to magic are affected more severely by this torii. The same phenomenon happened when we entered the Sea of Mist at Iris Cloud back then.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: The magical power of these torii affects Nishiki folks the most. It feels like strong magic power is flooding into the ears and tail.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: That's why the M. Nishiki people didn't chase Miyako. It's not that they didn't chase her, it's that they couldn't chase her.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: So Miyako is just like you now, Yoshino? Wandering around these mountains, exhausted?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yes, think so.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Miyako is suffering more, likely. Miyako is more sensitive to bad magic than Yoshino...

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Sensitive to bad magic is terrible. It means that you are more likely to accept harmful things directly.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: When Miyako was trapped by ever-darkness near the Metro Hole, she touched the ever-darkness with her own magic and searched the area. No normal person could have done that.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Even if they could, they wouldn't do it.'

Name: Putra
Phrase: Fearlessness is a problem when it goes too far.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: But there are many missions that cannot be accomplished without people like that. Of the fearless people, some are good soldiers, and some who are not.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Miyako is a good soldier, I guess...?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: I don't think a good soldier would be this reckless.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Yes, what Miyako did was dangerous, but I don't think she jumped in without a plan.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: What makes you say that?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Miyako decided that 'I can manage on my own'. That's why she didn't recruit a companion from among the Railway Army.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Miyako took advantage of this torii labyrinth. So that she wouldn't be stopped from doing anything stupid. So that her people wouldn't follow her.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Come to think of it, the Railway Army didn't seem to have a good grasp of what happened when Miyako disappeared.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: It could be that she really got lost and was left behind. But with everyone but Miyako having made it out safely, it's quite a surprise that she's the only one who couldn't make it back.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: When the troops retreated, the Mist had cleared and there was no battle with monsters. If Miyako was walking at the tail end of the line, there must have been someone close by as long as they were in formation.

Name: Putra
Phrase: This means, she gradually moved away from the ranks.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: That's only my guess. Miyako seems smarter than Versailles. I wonder if she might do something like that.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: ...Heh, that's what Yoshino wanted to say.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yakky-tan is an esper? Can you read Yoshino's mind?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: If I could read your mind, I wouldn't have any trouble. I just thought that a smart soldier would have deduced this.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Because I am also a smart and brave soldier.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Oooh- Yakky-tan is clever, cute.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: I'm not cute, I'm brave!

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Really? Yakky-tan is quite a scaredy-cat too?

Name: Putra
Phrase: One yes vote from the right.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: One yes vote from the left.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: You're all annoying! I'm the officer in the Eisengrad Northern Army, remember? I've been through a lot more Hell than all of you!

Name: Putra
Phrase: You have the image of a woman who is strong in the battlefield, yet scared of ghosts.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: T-That's not true at all. How can I, the Great Yakutsk have any weaknesses? I am ready to take on anything, be it a monster or a Nishikese youkai.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Heh, so you can't fight a cursed Nishikese doll, but you can fight a youkai?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Naturally. First of all, youkai and Mist Monsters aren't even the same. Youkai are folklore creatures where humans find them interesting and turned them into stories...

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Um, Miss Yakutsk, you should look behind for a moment?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: What? Are you trying to scare me too, Queensway?

Name: Queensway
Phrase: No, it's no youkai, it's a fox.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Huh? What do you mean, a fox? Why would I be afraid of a fox? I sleep with one every night. I wouldn't be surprised even if it had nine tails and breathed fire...

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: GWAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH!
It's not a surprise for the fox tail-loving Yakutsk to be so startled that she crashed into one of the pillars of the torii.
Yakutsk turned her head to see a girl wearing a fox mask floating in the air. She suddenly appeared on the spot, without a sound or sign of life.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: F-F-F-F-F-FO-FO-FOX FOX FOX MASK HERE! IT WAS SO CLOSE THAT IT ALMOST TOUCHED MY EYES AND NOSE!

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Calm down, Yakky-tan. What you saw was not a fox mask, but a girl wearing a fox mask. You were just a little too close.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Huh? A girl?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Really...

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Well, it's hard to say it's normal when she's floating in the air.

Name: Fox Masked Girl
Phrase: Miyako is just up ahead. She's worried about being alone, so you'll have to follow her.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: She's gone!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: She knew Miyako's name. She doesn't seem to be a Mist Monster...

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Un, felt nothing bad from her at all

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: She was pointing to the right. So if we take that branch to the right, we'll find Miyako, is that it?

Name: Putra
Phrase: But didn't we already went that branch there on the right many times?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: If we go there 'now', we'll be on the right path. Yoshino thinks that's what she was trying to tell us.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Let's go. If we pass through that torii, we will surely find a new path.

Following the guidance of the fox-masked Nishikese girl, we passed through the torii on the right and continued onwards. Then, just as Yoshino said, a path that had never been seen before came into view.
But it was shrouded in a very thick Mist. Many Mist Monsters awaited us...
